; Regression test for issue #597: If total transaction in a budgeted account equals zero... (BZ#597)
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/597
;
; When actual transactions in a budgeted account sum to zero (e.g., a purchase
; and a return that cancel each other out), the budget percentage calculation
; must handle the zero numerator without errors. The original bug caused a
; division error when computing percentage; the fix added quantity() wrappers
; and a guard against zero denominators.

~ Monthly
    Expenses:Food    $100
    Assets:Checking

2024/01/01 Buy food
    Expenses:Food    $50.00
    Assets:Checking

2024/01/15 Return food
    Expenses:Food    $-50.00
    Assets:Checking

test budget --period "2024/01"
           0     $-100.00      $100.00     0  Assets:Checking
           0      $100.00     $-100.00     0  Expenses:Food
------------ ------------ ------------ -----
           0            0            0     0
end test
